  "prompt": "What are the documents required for a uneducated person if he doesn't have birth certificate?",
  "response": "For an uneducated person without a birth certificate, the following alternative documents can be used to establish age and identity:\n\n1. Alternative Age Proof Documents:\n- Aadhar Card\n- School Leaving Certificate\n- Passport\n- PAN Card\n- Voter ID Card\n- Ration Card\n- Municipal Corporation Certificate\n- Affidavit from a Gazetted Officer\n- Electoral Photo Identity Card (EPIC)\n- Bank Passbook\n- Senior Citizen Card\n\n2. Additional Supporting Documents:\n- Affidavit from parents/guardians\n- Declaration by local village/ward head\n- Medical records\n- Baptism/Birth registration certificate\n- School admission register\n- Church/Religious institution records\n\n3. Sworn Affidavit Process:\n- Create an affidavit stating date of birth\n- Get it notarized\n- Signed by two witnesses\n- Includes details like name, parents' names, place of birth\n\n4. Government Helpline/Assistance:\n- Seek help from local government offices\n- Approach Gram Panchayat or Municipal Corporation\n- Consult local legal aid centers\n\nNote: Specific requirements might vary depending on the state and purpose of identification.",
